# Coaching Corner — keep the roadmap current

Any time you build, change, or extend the Coaching Corner, you MUST update
[docs/COACHING_CORNER_ROADMAP.md](../../docs/COACHING_CORNER_ROADMAP.md) in the same change. This doc is the canonical, durable record of what exists and why.

Update it when you:
- add or alter a `coaching.*` migration (new table/column/enum) → reflect it in Part 5 (data model) and the mermaid diagram.
- add or change a coach/member endpoint or helper → reflect it in Part 6 (backend surface).
- add or change a coach panel / member tab / shared store → reflect it in Part 7 (frontend surface).
- complete or advance a phase → flip its status (✅/🟡/⬜) in the snapshot and phase sections.
- make a non-obvious architectural decision → add it to Part 4 with the rationale ("why"), since this doc preserves intent for posterity.

Keep edits accurate and grounded in the actual code (cite real file paths, table/column, and endpoint names). Do not let the doc drift from reality. Do NOT edit transient plan files under `.cursor/plans/` as a substitute — this doc is the source of truth.
